+
+In our Hyde Park workshop, we see this dilemma weekly. Clients arrive convinced they need a new computer or phone. Nine times out of ten, we can repair the keyboard for a fraction of that cost, and have them back to work within days. This guide walks you through the real decision: when repair makes sense, when replacement does, and what to expect in Johannesburg.
+
+## How Much Does Keyboard Repair Actually Cost?
+
+The first question is always price. Let's be direct: keyboard repair is almost always cheaper than replacement.
+
+We start with a R599 assessment. This gives us a clear picture of what's wrong, whether it's a stuck key, liquid damage, a faulty cable, or a logic-board issue. After that diagnosis, repair costs depend entirely on the device and fault.
+
+For most MacBook keyboards, the repair falls within a confirmed range once we've examined it. iPhone and iPad keyboard issues (which are usually screen-related) vary by model and severity. The point: you won't know your exact cost until we assess, but repair is reliably a fraction of buying new.
+
+Replacing an entire MacBook or iPhone, by contrast, costs thousands. A new MacBook Air sits around R25,000 upwards. A new iPhone Pro is R15,000+. Even refurbished devices rarely drop below R8,000. Repair, in nearly every scenario, wins on cost alone.
+
+## Why Johannesburg Workshops Often Beat Apple's Quote
+
+Apple's official repair service quotes are notoriously high. We've seen quotes for R8,000-R12,000 for keyboard replacements that we handle for a fraction of that.
+
+Three reasons:
+
+**First, we diagnose before we quote.** Apple's authorised service centres often bundle keyboard issues into larger repairs or assume logic-board involvement when it's just a cable. We open the device, find the actual fault, and quote only what's needed.
+
+**Second, our turnaround is faster.** Many Johannesburg clients tell us Apple quoted three to four weeks. We typically turn keyboards around within 5-7 working days, often faster. Load shedding affects us like everyone else, but we've built our schedule around it.
+
+**Third, our warranty is genuine.** We offer up to a 3-year warranty on keyboard repairs (depending on the fault type and device). If the keyboard fails again under warranty, we fix it at no charge. Apple's warranty covers defects, yes, but the initial quote is still eye-watering.
+
+This isn't about undercutting. It's about efficiency. We've repaired over 15,000 devices in the Johannesburg area. We know MacBook keyboards inside out.
+
+## When Repair Is the Right Choice
+
+**Your keyboard has a single-point failure:** One or two keys don't work, or the whole keyboard is unresponsive. The rest of your device functions normally.
+
+**Your device is under three years old:** Older hardware sometimes isn't worth repairing (parts become scarce, labour costs rise relative to device value). Newer devices usually are.
+
