+## Why Your MacBook Pro 14 Inch Won't Power Up
+
+The cause matters because the cost and repair timeline depend entirely on it. A MacBook refusing to start could be a dead battery (fixable in hours), a faulty power adapter (sometimes just R599 assessment to confirm), or, at the worst end, a logic board failure requiring specialist component-level work.
+
+In our workshop, we see four categories repeatedly:
+
+**Dead or degraded battery.** Modern MacBook batteries lose capacity over time, and some fail suddenly. If your Mac won't boot even when plugged in, the battery may not be holding enough charge to trigger the Power Management Unit (PMU). This is the most straightforward repair and doesn't require board-level work.
