+**Liquid damage or corrosion.** Even if your Mac hasn't had a dramatic spill, moisture from Johannesburg's humidity or coffee vapour can seep into the logic board. Corrosion on power delivery traces prevents the board from initialising. We assess this visually and electrically, sometimes cleaning resolves it, sometimes component replacement is needed.
+
+**Logic board failure.** Capacitors fail, a GPU or CPU suffers thermal damage, or a power regulator dies. This requires component-level diagnosis and, in many cases, specialist repair or board replacement.
