+Your MacBook Pro M1 sits dark on the desk. You've held the power button. Nothing. No Apple logo. No fan noise. No response. It's a sinking feeling, especially if you're relying on that machine for work or study in Johannesburg's unpredictable power climate.
+
+We've diagnosed this fault on more than 18,000 Apple devices since opening our Hyde Park workshop, and the M1 "won't turn on" issue is one of the most common calls we field. The good news: most of the time, it's fixable. The reality: the cause could be anything from a simple SMC reset to a failed logic board, and the only way to know is to get it on the bench.
