+## Frequently Asked Questions
+
+### Q: Will an SMC reset fix my M1 that won't turn on?
+
+An SMC (System Management Controller) reset can resolve power-delivery glitches on older MacBook models, but M1 Macs don't have a traditional SMC. Instead, they use the power button combo: hold power + Volume Up + Volume Down for 10 seconds. If your M1 shows no lights and doesn't respond to this, the issue is deeper than a firmware reset. We try this free of charge during diagnosis, but if it doesn't work, you'll need physical repair.
