+    author: 'courtney-bentley',
+    content: `# MacBook Pro M2 Liquid Damage Repair: What You Need to Know
+
+Liquid damage to a MacBook Pro M2 is one of the most stressful situations any Mac user can face. We have seen hundreds of devices arrive at our Hyde Park workshop after spills, condensation, or accidental water exposure, and the good news is that most are repairable. The key is understanding what happens when liquid enters your device, how much repair typically costs, and why speed matters.
+
+At ZA Support, we have repaired more than 18,000 MacBooks over the past decade, including countless M2 models affected by liquid damage. What we have learned is that the first 24 hours are critical. Corrosion begins immediately, but catching the damage early dramatically improves both the success rate and the final cost.
+
+## How Liquid Damage Affects Your MacBook Pro M2
+
+When liquid enters a MacBook Pro M2, it does not simply sit in one place. The device's logic board contains dozens of components operating at high voltages, processors, memory modules, power management circuits, and liquid creates conductive pathways between them. This causes short circuits, component burnout, and sometimes catastrophic failure within minutes.
+
+The M2 MacBook Pro models are particularly vulnerable because Apple has increased component density. Everything is closer together, which means corrosion spreads faster and repair work becomes more intricate. We have documented cases where a single spill caused damage across five separate circuit zones on the logic board.
+
+Humidity and load shedding in Johannesburg add another layer of complexity. If your device sits powered on during a spill, heat accelerates corrosion. If it sits unpowered for days during a power cut without proper drying, mineral deposits and oxidation take hold. This is why we always recommend powering off immediately and bringing the device in for assessment rather than attempting home drying techniques.
+
+## ZA Support's Assessment and Repair Process
+
+Our first step is always a detailed diagnostic assessment, which costs R599. During this assessment, we examine the logic board under magnification, test power delivery, and identify which components have been affected. We have invested in ultrasonic cleaning equipment and specialist microscopes specifically because early assessment prevents false starts and wasted labour.
+
+Once we understand the damage, we outline your options: component-level board repair, logic board replacement, or data recovery if the device will not power on. For many customers, our [logic board repair](/logic-board-repair) service restores full functionality at a fraction of Apple's replacement costs. We have successfully repaired M2 boards with extensive liquid damage that Apple's retail stores would have condemned outright.
+
+The timeline depends on severity. A light spill affecting only the keyboard area might take 2-3 working days. Deeper [liquid damage](/liquid-damage) affecting the power delivery circuits or main processor can take 5-7 days because we must carefully clean, test, and sometimes replace individual components. We quote turnaround times honestly at the assessment stage, no surprises.
+
+## Typical Costs and What Affects Pricing
+
+The R599 assessment is non-negotiable and applies to every liquid-damaged MacBook. After that, repair costs depend entirely on what we find.
+
+If corrosion is limited to the keyboard connector or a peripheral circuit, cleaning and minor component replacement typically runs between R800 and R2,000. If the damage has reached the main power delivery section or processor area, logic board replacement becomes necessary. Our replacement boards are sourced from verified refurbished stock and come with a 3-year warranty, far more affordable than purchasing a new M2 MacBook Pro.
+
+Data recovery is a separate service, charged at R2,999, and applies if your drive is intact but inaccessible due to logic board failure. Most M2 MacBook Pros have soldered storage, so recovery is complex but possible. We have successfully extracted data from more than 12,000 devices over our history.
+
+We never quote vague ranges like "R2,800 to R3,500." Every quote is confirmed after we assess your device and understand the actual scope of work. This transparency is why so many customers in Hyde Park and surrounding suburbs trust us with their expensive equipment.
+
+## Prevention and What to Do Right Now
+
+If your MacBook Pro M2 has been exposed to liquid, here is what matters:
+
+Power it off immediately. Do not attempt to use it. Do not leave it plugged in. Do not place it in rice or expose it to direct heat. Simply close the lid and bring it to us.
+
+If your device is still working, back up your data to an external drive or cloud service before bringing it in. We will not damage your data during repair, but it is your insurance policy.
+
+Liquid damage claims are rarely covered under standard Apple Care, so do not expect warranty support. However, our repairs are typically 40-60% less expensive than Apple's out-of-warranty logic board replacement.
+
+For future prevention, consider investing in a quality protective case and keeping your MacBook away from drinks and condensation-prone environments. We have also observed that devices used near windows during Johannesburg's humid summer months are more vulnerable to internal condensation, a hidden risk that many users overlook.
+
+## Why Speed Matters
+
+Every hour a liquid-damaged MacBook sits unpowered, minerals in the liquid begin to crystallise on the circuit board. Corrosion spreads. Components that might have been salvageable degrade further. We have seen repair costs triple because a device sat in a cupboard for a week before being assessed.
+
+Our workshop operates Monday to Friday, and we accept liquid-damaged devices by appointment. [Book online at zasupport.com/book](https://zasupport.com/book) to secure a same-day or next-day assessment slot. For urgent cases, [WhatsApp us on 064 529 5863](https://wa.me/27645295863) and we will advise on priority scheduling.
