+    author: 'courtney-bentley',
+    content: `# MacBook Pro M2 Logic Board Repair: What to Expect at ZA Support
+
+Your MacBook Pro M2 is a precision instrument, and when the logic board fails, the entire machine stops working. We understand the panic that sets in, you've lost access to your files, your workflow is halted, and you're wondering whether repair is even possible. At ZA Support in Hyde Park, Johannesburg, we have repaired logic board failures in more than 18,000 Apple devices over the past decade. The good news: most M2 logic board issues are repairable, and the cost is significantly lower than replacing the entire machine.
+
+This guide covers what happens when an M2 logic board fails, what we can do about it, and how our workshop in Johannesburg handles these complex repairs.
+
+## What Goes Wrong with MacBook Pro M2 Logic Boards?
+
+The logic board is the central nervous system of your MacBook Pro. Every function, from powering on, to charging, to running your applications, depends on it. When we assess M2 models at our Hyde Park workshop, the most common failures we see fall into a few categories.
+
+**Liquid damage** remains the leading cause. A spilled coffee, a water bottle left on the desk during load shedding, or even humidity from Johannesburg's summer rains can seep into the ports and corrode the board's circuitry. The damage is often invisible at first, your Mac might work for days before a short circuit takes the whole system down.
+
+**Power delivery failures** are the second most common issue. The M2's power management chip handles the delicate balance of delivering exactly the right voltage to the processor. When this fails, your MacBook won't turn on, or it powers off randomly. We have seen this happen after a failed firmware update or, occasionally, from a manufacturing defect in very early M2 units.
+
+**Component failures** account for the remainder. A capacitor fails. A power IC burns out. These are microscopic failures, but they cascade through the board's circuits and bring the whole system to a halt.
+
+Each of these requires a different approach to diagnosis and repair.
+
+## ZA Support's M2 Logic Board Repair Process
+
+We don't guess when it comes to logic board repairs. Our assessment begins with visual inspection under magnification, we look for burnt components, corrosion, or physical damage that might explain the symptoms. Then we move to diagnostic testing.
+
+Most M2 boards are repairable once we identify what failed. If a capacitor blew, we replace it. If a power IC is damaged, we remove the faulty chip and install a functioning one. If liquid damage has spread across multiple layers, we clean the board using our ultrasonic cleaning process, dry it thoroughly, and run diagnostics again.
+
+The entire process, from arrival to diagnosis, repair, and testing, typically takes 5-7 working days. If data recovery is also needed (which we handle separately), add another 3-5 days.
+
+Our repair comes with a 3-year warranty on the logic board itself. If the same failure recurs within three years, we repair or replace it at no cost.
+
+## Cost and Turnaround Times
+
+Assessment of your M2 starts at R599. This fee covers diagnostic testing, microscopic inspection, and a written quote for the repair itself.
+
+Logic board repairs, once assessed, are quoted based on what we find. Some repairs, replacing a failed capacitor or power IC, fall on the lower end. Others, where multiple components have failed or rework is extensive, cost more. We confirm the exact price after inspection, never before.
+
+If you've experienced liquid damage, our [liquid damage repair service](/liquid-damage) includes board cleaning, corrosion treatment, and full component testing. If your drive has failed alongside the logic board, we offer [data recovery](/data-recovery) from R2,999.
+
+Once we begin repair, turnaround is 5-7 working days for most boards. Rush service is available, discuss this when you [contact us](/contact).
+
+Many clients are surprised to learn that our repair costs far less than a new MacBook Pro. Even a top-tier M2 14-inch model costs over R45,000 new. Most logic board repairs are completed for a fraction of that figure.
+
+## Why Choose ZA Support Over Mail-In or DIY Repair?
+
+Mail-in services to Johannesburg's airports create risk. Your Mac spends days in transit, exposed to humidity and temperature changes. We're local, you bring your device to our Hyde Park workshop, and we begin diagnostics the same day.
+
+DIY repair is tempting, but M2 boards are not hobbyist territory. The components are millimetres apart. Rework requires a specialised rework station that heats the board to precise temperatures. One wrong movement, and you've destroyed a R15,000 board. We've seen more than a few machines arrive at our door after an unsuccessful DIY attempt, and the secondary damage always costs more to fix.
+
+Apple's authorised repair? Apple will quote you R8,000-R12,000 for logic board replacement alone, plus labour. They don't repair boards; they replace them. You'll also wait 2-3 weeks for parts.
+
+Our [logic board repair service](/logic-board-repair) gives you a working machine, in your hands, within a week, at a fraction of Apple's price.
