+## Frequently Asked Questions
+
+### Q: How do I know if my M2's logic board is actually the problem?
+
+If your MacBook won't power on, shuts down randomly, charges intermittently, or shows the "?" folder on startup, the logic board may be involved, but it's not the only possibility. Bring it to us. We run full diagnostics, and the R599 assessment will pinpoint what's failed. Many times, a simpler fix (like a faulty charging cable or corrupted firmware) is the real culprit, and we'll tell you that too.
+
