+## Why Your MacBook Pro M3 Stops Responding
+
+The M3 generation, released in early 2024, is generally reliable hardware, but several common culprits can cause a complete power failure:
+
+**Power delivery issues** are the most frequent. The USB-C power adapter degrades over time, or the charging port itself becomes obstructed with dust and lint. Johannesburg's dry highveld climate means static and dust accumulation happens faster than you'd expect. We've pulled out compacted lint the size of a small pebble from ports that looked fine to the naked eye.
+
+**Logic board faults** come next. These range from failed power management circuits, typically caused by thermal stress or liquid exposure, to manufacturing defects in the M3 chip itself. Rarer, but we do see them.
+
+**Battery degradation** can also trigger complete shutdown in older M3 units. When a MacBook's battery fails catastrophically, the power management system can lock the entire device in a protective state. This is less common in 2024 machines, but load shedding and unstable power in Sandton and surrounding areas means some clients' Macs have endured chaotic charging cycles.
+
+**Liquid damage**, spilled coffee, rain exposure, or even humidity from Cape Town summers, causes immediate power failure. We handle over 12,000 MacBook repairs annually, and liquid damage accounts for roughly 30% of our "won't turn on" cases.
+
+## Our Diagnostic Process at ZA Support
+
+When you bring your M3 into our Hyde Park workshop, we don't guess. Here's exactly what happens:
+
+First, we run a **physical inspection**. We look for visible liquid damage, corrosion around ports, or obvious impact damage. We check the charging cable and adapter, you'd be surprised how often the problem sits in your bag, not your Mac.
+
