+
+If power delivery is fine, we apply **forced reset procedures**. The M3 responds to a specific key sequence: press and hold power for 30 seconds, release, wait 5 seconds, then press power again. This clears the power management controller's memory. Many devices wake up at this point. If yours does, we've diagnosed a software glitch, not hardware failure.
+
+If forced reset fails, we move to **bench diagnostics**. We connect your MacBook to specialised testing equipment that can communicate with the logic board even when the display won't activate. This reveals whether the CPU is responding, whether RAM is addressable, and whether we're looking at a battery issue, power management failure, or something deeper.
+
+Our assessment fee is R599, and if you proceed with repair, that fee applies toward your final invoice.
+
+## Common M3 Repairs We Handle
+
+**Charging port replacement** is routine. The USB-C connector is a wear item, 1,000+ insertions and micro-fractures develop. We replace it with a genuine Apple component, and your Mac charges normally again. Turnaround is 2-3 days.
+
+**Power adapter replacement** costs confirmed after assessment, but genuine adapters are available for most M3 configurations. Many clients opt for this first.
+
+**Logic board repair**, when the power management circuit has failed, involves micro-soldering or chip replacement. This is precise work. Our technicians complete more than 15,000 device repairs across all product lines annually, so we have the experience. Costs and turnaround depend on damage severity, confirmed after diagnostics.
+
+**Battery replacement** resolves many cases where the power management system is locking the device for safety. MacBook batteries are R2,500 upwards, and replacement takes 1-2 days.
+
+For devices affected by **liquid damage**, we offer full repair or [data recovery services](/liquid-damage) if the logic board cannot be salvaged. Data recovery costs from R2,999, and we can usually retrieve your files even from severely corroded boards.
+
